<P>And let me a&s;k you, Mr. Lovelace, &s;aid the Cap|tain; yet not &s;o much from doubt, as that I may pro|ceed upon &s;ure grounds&mdash;You are <HI>willing</HI> to co-ope|rate with my dear friend in a general reconciliation?</P>
<P>Let me tell you, Mr. Tomlin&s;on, that if it can be di&s;tingui&s;hed, that my readine&s;s to make up with a family, of who&s;e genero&s;ity I have not had rea&s;on to think highly, is intirely owing to the value I have for this angel of a woman, I will not only co-operate with Mr. John Harlowe, as you a&s;k; but I will meet
